nodes.documentation:
Abstract base contract for token sales.

 * Handle
- start and end dates
- accepting investments
- minimum funding goal and refund
- various statistics during the crowdfund
- different pricing strategies
- different investment policies (require server side customer id, allow only whitelisted addresses)
nodes.name: CrowdsaleExt

nodes.documentation: Don't expect to just send in money and get tokens.

The basic entry point to participate the crowdsale process.

    * Pay for funding, get invested tokens back in the sender address.
nodes.name: buy

nodes.documentation: Allow anonymous contributions to this crowdsale.
nodes.name: invest

nodes.documentation:
Make an investment.

    * Crowdsale must be running for one to invest.
We must have not pressed the emergency brake.

    * @param receiver The Ethereum address who receives the tokens
@param customerId (optional) UUID v4 to track the successful payments on the server side
nodes.name: investInternal

nodes.documentation:
allocate tokens for the early investors.

    * Preallocated tokens have been sold before the actual crowdsale opens.
This function mints the tokens and moves the crowdsale needle.

    * Investor count is not handled; it is assumed this goes for multiple investors
and the token distribution happens outside the smart contract flow.

    * No money is exchanged, as the crowdsale team already have received the payment.

    * param weiPrice Price of a single full token in wei
nodes.name: allocate

nodes.documentation: Modified allowing execution only if the crowdsale is currently running.
nodes.name: inState

nodes.documentation:
Finalize a succcesful crowdsale.

    * The owner can triggre a call the contract that provides post-crowdsale actions, like releasing the tokens.
nodes.name: finalize

nodes.documentation:
Allow to (re)set finalize agent.

    * Design choice: no state restrictions on setting this, so that we can fix fat finger mistakes.
nodes.name: setFinalizeAgent

nodes.documentation: Allow addresses to do early participation.
nodes.name: setEarlyParticipantWhitelist

nodes.documentation:
Allow crowdsale owner to close early or extend the crowdsale.

    * This is useful e.g. for a manual soft cap implementation:
- after X amount is reached determine manual closing

    * This may put the crowdsale to an invalid state,
but we trust owners know what they are doing.
nodes.name: setEndsAt

nodes.documentation:
Allow to (re)set pricing strategy.

    * Design choice: no state restrictions on the set, so that we can fix fat finger mistakes.
nodes.name: setPricingStrategy

nodes.documentation:
Allow to (re)set Token.
@param _token upgraded token address
nodes.name: setCrowdsaleTokenExtv1

nodes.documentation:
Allow to change the team multisig address in the case of emergency.

    * This allows to save a deployed crowdsale wallet in the case the crowdsale has not yet begun
(we have done only few test transactions). After the crowdsale is going
then multisig address stays locked for the safety reasons.
nodes.name: setMultisig

nodes.documentation: @return true if the crowdsale has raised enough money to be a successful.
nodes.name: isMinimumGoalReached

nodes.documentation: Check if the contract relationship looks good.
nodes.name: isFinalizerSane

nodes.documentation: Check if the contract relationship looks good.
nodes.name: isPricingSane

nodes.documentation:
Crowdfund state machine management.

    * We make it a function and do not assign the result to a variable, 
so there is no chance of the variable being stale.
nodes.name: getState

nodes.documentation: Interface marker.
nodes.name: isCrowdsale

nodes.documentation:
Check if the current invested breaks our cap rules.

    *
The child contract must define their own cap setting rules.
We allow a lot of flexibility through different capping strategies (ETH, token count)
Called from invest().
 
@param tokensSoldTotal What would be our total sold tokens count after this transaction

    * @return true if taking this investment would break our cap rules
nodes.name: isBreakingCap

nodes.documentation: Check if the current crowdsale is full and we can no longer sell any tokens.
nodes.name: isCrowdsaleFull

nodes.documentation: Create new tokens or transfer issued tokens to the investor depending on the cap model.
nodes.name: assignTokens
